summary: i think it’s a frustration post, however you want to interpret it
body:
i think it’s a frustration post, however you want to interpret it

so i love some shit no one i know also loves or even likes:

- marvel

- peaky blinders

- sherlock

- brooklyn nine-nine

- old(er) music (like eighties/nineties music but also from 2005-2013)

- the actors who play in those things like: sebastian stan, rdj, cevans, cillian murphy, finn and joe cole

and i can’t even tell people - people who i call my friends - that anymore because they just start shouting at me like ‘no one cares’ and ‘shut up’ and ‘that is boring’ and stuff like that

those people like shit like:

- riverdale

- brugklas (something dutch it’s this weird thing. you can maybe compare it to degrassi or sumn)

- to all the boys i’ve loved before

- sierra burgess is a loser

- kissing booth

- the actors who play in it: noah centineo, cole sprouse, kj apa and jacob elordi

- the new music of this time

but when i say i don’t really like those things they say like ‘hOw Do YOu eVeN HaVE aN OpiNiON oN THesE tHinGs, YOu doN’t eVeN kNow tHEm’ and they start bashing me for giving my opinion on things i apparently know nothing about

let me tell you: i have seen every thing they like and i’m not gonna lie i did like it but i’ve moved on and started liking other shit but i still respect them and the things they like but my point is i do know what i’m talking about so i can have a proper opinion on those things and i can’t say that they have seen anything of the things i like

i listen to them everytime they start about the things they like and say ‘oohh yes’ or sumn but the second i say like ‘you know the new avengers 4 trailer is coming out soon!!’ or ‘something funny happened in this ep of b99’ all say like yes we know stop please

this also happened today we were just talking and someone started about riverdale and she said how much she liked it and i said ‘oh i don’t really like it anymore it’s gotten a bit boring’ and she immediately started bashing me saying like ‘and i don’t care what you think’ and ‘you don’t even watch it’ and then my friend said ‘you only watch pEaKY BliNdErS’ and she started mocking me with it and then someone came and i had gotten quiet because i was already having one of my worst days in this year and she asked if everything was ok with me and the same friend who started mocking me said ‘no she’s mad because she likes peaky blinders and we don’t’ and i left because i was feeling so shitty the whole day and then they started shitting even more on me

i went to my other friends and i just started crying and i love my friends to who i went because they really helped me and also the girl who asked me how i was doing, thanks for asking because no one else did and also the girl who was sitting in front of me because she also asked but i said i was totally fine and also my best friends who listen to me anytime i start again rambling about the things i like

i love my two best friends so much they mock me too sometimes but they don’t do it like every other day and they help me through all my shit

i also decided to never tell my problems to anyone anymore because everything i say is being used against me and i’m really done with it and the person i usually tell it to has her own shit and to be frank she doesn’t really care…

summary: ————————————————————— Voicemail #23 To: Tony Stark From: Peter Parker May’s not dating Gene anymore.  I know I called you a...
body:
—————————————————————

Voicemail #23

To: Tony Stark

From: Peter Parker

May’s not dating Gene anymore.

I know I called you a little while ago but I just need to tell someone, y’know?

She called me into the living room, just her and me, and when I asked where Gene was, she told me that he left. I asked “why?”, ‘cause Gene had been saying at dinner that they should watch a movie or something. May kinda smiled a bit, but not one of those ‘I’m so happy’ smiles, one of those sad ones.

She told me she broke up with him, Mr. Stark.

I wasn’t expecting that at all, and I told her so, and she said to me that they were never really dating in the first place. She said that they were kinda maybe dating, it just took her a bit to realize it.

She told me that she wasn’t ready to date after all, that she needed some time, and that she was sorry.

I asked her, “sorry for what?”

She said she was sorry that she didn’t tell me about all of it- that she was scared. Scared about what I would say, how I would react, I guess. She told me that she had no reason to be scared after all, and that I was the perfect nephew she could have wished for.

…

But the thing is, she doesn’t really know what I was thinking. She didn’t hear that- that voicemail I left you.

But if she were to hear it… I want her to know that I’m sorry too. I was unfair and mean- and I didn’t even think about her at all, only me. 

The thing is, she’s great. She’s the absolute best. And she’s got her way with dealing with it all, just like I’ve got mine.

So you know what? When she does start dating someone, or maybe when she decides that she doesn’t want to at all, I’m gonna be there for her.

But since I can’t really tell her all that, I thought I’d tell you, Mr. Stark. I don’t know if you listened this far, or if you even listened to it at all, but it doesn’t really matter. I’m just glad I got to say all of this.

I’ll talk to you later, Mr Stark. Bye.

—————————————————————

tags: this is rly short but also! i love them
summary: the morning was still asleep around them, dim and slow and peaceful, quiet in the way tony’s days hadn't been in such a long...
body:
the morning was still asleep around them, dim and slow and peaceful, quiet in the way tony’s days hadn’t been in such a long time. pepper’s head on his chest was a comfortable weight, familiar like the rasp of metal beneath his fingers and a cool breeze over warm sand and breaking waves.

her fingers, careful and slow, traced his ribcage, dancing over bone and tracing the pattern of scars that the palladium had left behind.

(the wave crested, crashed down, curling neatly over and around him, as it sang with burning adoration just behind his ribs, aching to be free,)

an easy breath slipped from tony’s chest, light and free, as he carded his fingers through pepper’s hair carefully.

she smiled up at him, shifting slightly to meet his eyes, warm and bright in the room’s fragile emptiness.

(and tony nearly drowned under it, the swell of love blooming in his chest and shattering through his lungs, his breath catching under its weight.)

he curled up a few tiny inches to press a kiss to the crown of her head, smiling into her hair as his veins raced warm with love.

(and tony nearly drowned under it, the swell of love blooming in his chest and shattering through his lungs, his breath catching under its weight.)

he curled up a few tiny inches to press a kiss to the crown of her head, smiling into her hair as his veins raced warm with love.

trail.content_raw:
the morning was still asleep around them, dim and slow and peaceful, quiet in the way tony’s days hadn’t been in such a long time. pepper’s head on his chest was a comfortable weight, familiar like the rasp of metal beneath his fingers and a cool breeze over warm sand and breaking waves.

her fingers, careful and slow, traced his ribcage, dancing over bone and tracing the pattern of scars that the palladium had left behind.

(the wave crested, crashed down, curling neatly over and around him, as it sang with burning adoration just behind his ribs, aching to be free,)

title: Battle Scars
body:
So my next series picked itself. I wrote the first chapter for a challenge and it obviously needed more parts. This will have it’s own tag list. Marvel and All the Things members, let me know if you don’t want to be on it. Everyone else, let me know if you do.

You live in a world where soulmates share each other’s scars. Like most, you bore the typical minor wounds that barely even caught your attention. Until the day a large scar appears in the center of your chest. And this is no ordinary scar. 

Finding your soulmate is one thing. Admitting to him who you are is quite another.

I’m horrible at summaries. Sorry. Tony Stark x Reader. Soulmate AU! First part goes up tomorrow.

title: Espionage
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2rd7Zhq

by brvnnhilde

The mission was simple: seduce a super hero, sneak into the most secure facility in the world, steal an intelligence file from the earth’s mightiest heroes, and get out without anyone noticing. Nothing you hadn’t done a hundred times before–give or take a few details. But what you hadn’t counted on was that, for the first time in your five year career as an espionage agent, you might get caught.

Thrown into the middle of the conflict amongst the Avengers brought about by the Sokovia Accords, you struggle to navigate the toxic whirlwind of a war between friends while fighting an internal war of your own. And when the secrets of your past fall into the hands of a certain billionaire, your future–unfathomable and just out of reach– hangs in the balance.

Sides are chosen and loyalties tested, and you begin to discover that matters of the heart cannot be solved by logic or force, but rather by yielding to your inherent desires.
